  <title>Linear Transformations</title>

  <introduction>
    <p> Given a matrix <m>A</m>, how does <m>A</m> affect the vectors we apply it to? To fully understand linear systems of the form <m>A\mathbf{x}=\mathbf{b}</m> and their solution sets, we first need to see how <m>A</m> acts on vectors. </p>
